{"componentChunkName":"component---src-pages-telemetry-index-js","path":"/telemetry/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"securecodebox-telemetry-data\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#securecodebox-telemetry-data\" aria-label=\"securecodebox telemetry data permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>secureCodeBox Telemetry Data</h1>\n<p>The secureCodeBox Operator collects and submits anonymized data to give the development team a vague overview on how much the secureCodeBox is actually used.</p>\n<h2 id=\"datapoints-collected\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#datapoints-collected\" aria-label=\"datapoints collected permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Datapoints Collected:</h2>\n<p>The total number of datapoints collected is extremely small, and they are individually evaluated to ensure that the submitted data is as anonymous as possible.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Installed version of the secureCodeBox Operator (e.g. <code>v2.0.0</code>)</li>\n<li>List of installed ScanTypes across all kubernetes Namespaces: (e.g. <code>['nmap', 'zap-baseline']</code>). Unofficial ScanTypes are reported as <code>other</code>, to avoid submission of confidential data.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"collection-interval\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#collection-interval\" aria-label=\"collection interval permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Collection Interval</h2>\n<p>The data is submitted every 24 hours. When the Operator starts, the first data-point is submitted one hour after the start, to give users the opportunity to disable the telemetry data submission before the first datapoints are send.</p>\n<h2 id=\"disabling-telemetry-data-submission\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#disabling-telemetry-data-submission\" aria-label=\"disabling telemetry data submission permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Disabling Telemetry Data Submission</h2>\n<p>The collection of telemetry data can be completely disabled by setting the <code>telemetryEnabled</code> to <code>false</code>, e.g:</p>\n<deckgo-highlight-code language=\"bash\"  terminal=\"carbon\" theme=\"cobalt\" >\n          <code slot=\"code\">helm install securecodebox-operator secureCodeBox/operator --set=&quot;telemetryEnabled=false&quot;</code>\n        </deckgo-highlight-code>\n<h2 id=\"telemetry-code\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#telemetry-code\" aria-label=\"telemetry code permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Telemetry Code</h2>\n<p>The entire code for both the telemetry backend and frontend is open-source and linked below.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Telemetry Client used in secureCodeBox Operator: <a href=\"https://github.com/secureCodeBox/secureCodeBox-v2/blob/master/operator/internal/telemetry/telemetry.go\">telemetry client</a></li>\n<li>Telemetry Backend: <a href=\"https://github.com/secureCodeBox/telemetry\">telemetry backend</a></li>\n</ul>"}},"pageContext":{}}}